<TITLE> CJ withdraws from hearing Awal's appeal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 12 (bdnews24.com)  Chief justice MM Ruhul Amin on Thursday withdrew himself from the hearing of the appeal by acting law secretary Kazi Habibul Awal to overturn the High Court judgment that declared his appointment illegal. A full bench of the Appellate Division headed by Justice Amin adjourned the hearing of the appeal until Feb. 23 when the other members of the bench will hear it. The chief justice withdrew himself from the hearing following concerns raised by the appellant, Awal, in light of the representations made to the chief justice against the acting law secretary by a section of lower court judicial officers, . The High Court declared Awal's appointment illegal on Feb. 18, 2008 upon a writ petition filed by District and Sessions Judge Aftab Uddin Ahmed. The Appellate Division on March 6 granted Awal leave to appeal and stayed the judgement. Judge Ahmed filed the writ petition on July 5, 2007 challenging the appointment of Awal as acting law secretary. The government appointed Awal as acting law secretary on June 28, 2007. Barrister Amir-Ul Islam moved the appeal for Awal, while Azmalul Hossain appeared for petitioner. Azmalul told reporters the chief justice would not hear the apppeal but the other members of the appeals bench would
